data.description: Data for which you would like the kth raw moments. Atomic data type must be float.

lower.description: Estimated minimum possible value of the statistic. Only useful for the snapping mechanism.

upper.description: Estimated maximum possible value of the statistic. Only useful for the snapping mechanism.

name: dp_raw_moment

mechanism.description: Privatizing mechanism to use. Data type must be string. Value must be one of [`Automatic`, `Laplace`, `Snapping`, `Gaussian`, `AnalyticGaussian`]. `Automatic` chooses `Snapping` if protect floating point enabled, otherwise chooses `Laplace`.

privacy_usage.description: Object describing the type and amount of privacy to be used for the mechanism release. Atomic data type value must be float. Example value: {'epsilon': 0.5}

return.description: Differentially private sample estimate of kth raw moment for each column of the data.

description: Returns differentially private sample estimate of a raw moment for each column of the data.
